                        "ECOA section 701(e)(5) requires that, at the time of application, the creditor \u201cnotify an applicant in writing of the right to receive a copy of each written appraisal and valuation\u201d under section 701(e). Accordingly, the Bureau proposed in section 1002.14(a)(2) that, not later than the third business day after the creditor receives an application subject to \u00a7 1002.14(a)(1), a creditor shall provide an applicant with a written disclosure of the applicant's right to receive a copy of all appraisals and other written valuations developed in connection with such application."
