                        "As discussed above, for clarity and to be consistent with other similar regulatory requirements under TILA and RESPA, the Bureau proposed that \u00a7 1002.14(a)(1) use the term \u201cconsummation\u201d in place of the statutory term \u201cclosing.\u201d The Bureau proposed to define the term \u201cconsummation\u201d in \u00a7 1002.14(b)(1) as the time that a consumer becomes contractually obligated on a credit transaction. This definition mirrors the definition of the term provided in \u00a7 1026.2(a)(13) of Regulation Z.", 
